                                    <p class="indent">
                                        <em>Pamela Martin and Anne Neville (April 2016)</em><br />
                                        California law has historically prevented corporations from practicing medicine, which includes the employment of physicians. This long-standing ban on the corporate practice of medicine remains in effect, though the state has created a number of exceptions for certain types of organizations. This report explores the current state of the ban in California. It reviews the impact of the ban in a changing healthcare landscape that now emphasizes integrated service delivery, and explores the types of conflicts of interest &ndash; in addition to employment &ndash; that physicians and other medical professionals face. The report builds upon the policy options the Research Bureau discussed in its original 2007 paper.
                                    </p>
